    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_01_22_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Sussex-Place-24_ENK"/>24 Sussex Place</dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Mrs. Wilson.</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    Having been<lb/>
                    much harassed here and latterly<lb/>
                    called <del><unclear></unclear></del> for a time to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#STK">Scotland</placeName><lb/>
                    I must beg your <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">sister's</persName> pardon<lb/>
                    for not sending her until now the<lb/>
                    <choice><orig>inclosed</orig><reg>enclosed</reg></choice> memorandum, the tenor<lb/>
                    of which will I hope be found according<lb/>
                    to her wishes and intentions. I have<lb/>
                    no doubt the result will be £1200 in her<lb/>
                    pocket before the year elapses<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    In what state is <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title>? . and<lb/>
                    when may I hope for a copy. If it should<lb/>
                    be thought that a good long article in the<lb/>
                    <title ref="./Workography.xml#Quart1">Quarterly</title> would do better than the usual<lb/>
                    preliminary notices of the weekly literary<lb/>
                    papers, you could easily induce <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bentley</persName><lb/>
                    to consult <choice><orig>w<hi rend="superscript">h</hi></orig><reg>with</reg></choice>. <del>you</del> me as to the exact time<lb/>
                    of the publication - I mention this <choice><orig>be-<lb/>
                            -cause</orig><reg>because</reg></choice> as <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss E.</persName> will well understand<lb/>
                    it is not always found convenient<lb/>
                    in the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Quart1">Q R.</title> to insert <hi rend="underline">long</hi> papers on<lb/>
                    works which have just been plundered<lb/>
                    by the weekly journals; therefore I might<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_01_22_page02.jpg"/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    be obliged, in case of an opposite course<lb/>
                    being <del>taken</del> adopted, to defer handling<lb/>
                    <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> longer than would please my<lb/>
                    own feelings<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    I see I have not mentioned the<lb/>
                    sad cause of my absence in the<lb/>
                    North. I have this morning <choice><orig>re<lb/>
                    turned</orig><reg>returned</reg></choice> <unclear>thence</unclear> after burying a<lb/>
                    most dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockE1">mother</persName><lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    Ever yours sincerely<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">JG Lockhart</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        Copy<lb/>
                        22 Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi><lb/>
                        1834 Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi><lb/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1"><hi rend="underline">Lockhart</hi></persName><lb/>
                        <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1"><hi rend="underline">Helen</hi></title><lb/>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
